# Rust build artifacts — workspace builds everything into the root target/.
# Generated code (prost output) lives under target/ too, so it never gets committed;
# `cargo build` regenerates it from proto/wire.proto on any clone.
/target/
# Stray per-crate target dirs from building a single crate outside the workspace.
**/target/
**/*.rs.bk

# Visual Studio / Windows driver build artifacts (sensor/windows_driver).
# Per-config output dirs (x64/Debug, x64/Release, Win32/, ARM64/ ...) and caches.
**/.vs/
**/[Dd]ebug/
**/[Rr]elease/
**/x64/
**/Win32/
**/ARM64/
**/ipch/
*.obj
*.sys
*.pdb
*.ilk
*.exp
*.lib
*.tlog
*.log
*.lastbuildstate
*.idb
*.vcxproj.user
*.aps
*.opendb
*.suo
*.CppClean.log

# scratch / editor
.DS_Store
*.swp
